(96, 'AI notes: This transcript captures a reference check call with Rohit about Vishal, a former colleague from LiveSpace, followed by a discussion about Aptile''s upcoming product launch. Reference Check on Vishal Background and Role at LiveSpace - Vishal was among the first four team members at LiveSpace - Worked at LiveSpace for 5-6 years (2015-2021) - Grew from software engineer to director of engineering - Headed the CMS and pricing engine for on-demand construction of home interiors - Managed complex technical systems independently without much support Working Style and Strengths - Described as reliable, dependable, and level-headed - Technically outstanding and thoughtful in decision-making - Calm demeanor, especially during conflicts or heated discussions - More prepared and thoughtful before communicating ideas - Works well with different personalities in cross-functional settings - Considered among the top 5 team members Rohit has worked with Areas for Development - Not naturally charismatic or outspoken in communication - Might face challenges in business model development and identifying margin opportunities - As a technical founder, may need complementary skills for business aspects - Would benefit from hiring team members with complementary business skills Aptile Product Launch Discussion Action Items - [ ] Rohit to prepare and send early access package including: - [ ] Rahul and Mohit to help promote Aptile on LinkedIn (they have 110K and 50-55K followers respectivel...'),
(97, 'Received from Rahul - 2025-11-09: https://www.linkedin.com/in/ashishpratapdoshi/ <- CollektAI in Collections - came up in convo w/ CRED Cash Collections POC who Miten introduced me to Screen | P0 | POC: Rahul Mathur ---'),
(98, 'Received from Rahul - 2026-03-13: Building in Fintech - PFM with a great wedge. This is a short blurb: CA sees taxes, not investments.  Broker sees investments, not liabilities.  Bank sees balances, not goals. India''s 2 crore ₹30L+ income households have three advisors and no one who owns the outcome. Command is that entity. A personal finance agent that unifies accounts, loans, taxes, and investments and converts the full picture into proactive, executable actions. Before you ask. India''s Account Aggregator framework makes unified financial data real. AI makes continuous personalised optimisation possible. The financial rails are live. We''re building above every bank, broker, and insurer in India, the default decision layer for the end customer, the operating system for personal finance. Ankur Garg (Ex- Great Learning, Capital One, Morgan Stanley), Varun Gupta (Ex- Embibe, Ola, Linkedin) ---'),
(101, 'Background & Experience: - Previously at Microsoft in OfficeAI team, led voice experiences (grew to 6M users) - Led product work on Microsoft Designer team (AI-native design engine) - Worked at Prathyush as first PM (10th/11th employee) - Left in December to explore new opportunities
Market Strategy: - Targeting two segments: - Testing with both segments to identify common primitives - Sees opportunity in Canva’s current “bloated” state with AI features
Overall: Weak maybe: EO: 6-7 | Thesis: 5 | FMF: 6-7 | Archetype: 7-8 | Spike: 0.5 ++ Has the product spike but to omuch meandering SPC archetype with little focus on GTM ++ Is thoughtful and assimilates inputs and feedback ?? Wants to build a creation tool for creative agencies ?? Hasn’t spent much time. Thinking and prouct protype that she showed was poorere than first set of control net product workflows seen in AI community ?? Lacks the GTM muscle both for prosumer growth and b2b sales led ?? Wasn’t deeply calibrated on vairous plays beyond krea and more horizontal tools
Current Project Overview: - Building AI-native video editor with custom workflows - Key features: - Started development ~3 weeks ago - Testing with initial partners:
Technical Approach: - Focus on solving iteration challenges in AI generation - Built on open source models - Aims to reduce costs (target: significantly below current $100 cost for multi-tool workflows) - Integrates multiple capabilities:'),
(103, 'Prep 2026-03-19T23:33:00.000+05:30: Confluence Labs (YC W26) | confluence.sh What they do AI research lab building foundation models optimised for learning efficiency in data-sparse domains — drug design, materials science, hardware engineering, physics discovery. Their thesis: modern ML only excels where you can collect massive training data. In domains where data is expensive or slow to generate (physical experiments), current AI fails. Confluence''s approach: combine LLMs with discrete program synthesis to maximise what you can learn from a small number of experiments. Two-track strategy: 1. Hypothesis generation — AI that designs maximally informative experiments so each one teaches you the most 1. Data-efficient modelling — program synthesis + LLMs to make predictions with far fewer data points Technical milestone Came out of stealth with 97.9% on ARC-AGI-2 at $11.77/task — SOTA at launch (Feb 2026). ARC-AGI-2 is considered one of the hardest AI benchmarks in the world (tests novel reasoning from just a few examples). Approaching 100% on what was previously considered unsolvable. Open-sourced the solver. Backed by YC and Paul Graham personally. --- Founders 1. Brent Burdick (Co-Founder) — [LinkedIn not publicly indexed] 1. Niranjan Baskaran (Co-Founder) — linkedin.com/in/niranjan-baskaran-a906a5205 Both are extremely young (combined age ~43), no traditional industry pedigree — pure research talent profile. The Paul Graham backing is notable signal here.')
